<p>How do I pass a pointer to a C-style array to a template function?</p>  <p>The following doesn't compile with an error like <code>error: no matching function for call to 'func(char (*)[2])'</code></p>  <pre><code>// What do I need to change on the next line to make this compile? template&lt;typename T&gt; bool func(T **var) {     return var == 0; }  int main() {     char ar[2] = { 1, 2 };     func(&amp;ar);      return 0; } </code></pre>  <p><code>template&lt;typename T&gt; bool func(T *var[])</code> doesn't work either.</p>